A building
in the Durban CBD is on fire, resulting in multiple casualties, according to
paramedics on the scene. The fire
was reported at China Mall in West Street shortly after 10:00, said EMER-G-MED
spokesperson Kyle van Reenen. Speaking
from the scene, Van Reenen said paramedics had witnessed people trapped in the
building breaking windows and trying to climb out, in order to escape the
flames. Firefighters had been able to rescue these people, but others remained
trapped in the building. China Mall West street Durban is on fire. pic.twitter.com/xIf7yZ23nT  "The
fire is throughout the whole building, spreading floor by floor," said Van
